6. ğŸ” TROUBLESHOOTING
--------------------
âŒ If you encounter "No wireless interfaces found":
  â€¢ Ensure wireless adapter is properly connected
  â€¢ Check if adapter supports monitor mode
  â€¢ Try different USB port
  â€¢ Install appropriate drivers for your adapter

âŒ If you get permission errors:
  â€¢ Ensure you're running with sudo
  â€¢ Check file permissions
  â€¢ Verify user is in sudoers group

âŒ If monitor mode is stuck or wireless not working:
  â€¢ Stop monitor mode:
    $ sudo airmon-ng stop wlan0mon
  â€¢ Restart NetworkManager:
    $ sudo service NetworkManager restart
    or
    $ sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager

